Citation.sTitle: Gas phase PVTx properties for binary mixtures of HFC-161 and HFC-143a
Citation.sAbstract: An experimental study of the pressure volume temperature composition (PVTx) properties in the gas phase for binary mixtures of ethyl fluoride  (HFC-161) and 1,1,1-trifluoroethane (HFC-143a) was conducted in the range of temperatures from 308.138 to 403.205 K, pressures from 1077.3  to 4684.3 kPa, densities from 0.5144 to 2.0224 mol dm-3, and compositions from 0.3852 to 0.8703 mole fractions of HFC-161. The measurements  were performed with an isochoric cell apparatus. The uncertainties in the present work were estimated to be +-1.5 kPa for pressure, +-6mK for  temperature, and +-0.15% for composition. On the basis of the experimental PVTx property data, a truncated virial equation of state was developed  for the binary HFC-161/143a system. This equation reproduced the experimental data in the gas phase within +-0.247% in pressure and within  +-0.254% in density.
